# DAG Implementation in Python

## 📌 Overview
This project implements a **Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG)** in Python.

A DAG is a graph that:
- Has directed edges
- Contains no cycles

It is widely used in:
- Task scheduling
- Data pipelines
- Dependency resolution

---

## 🚀 Features
- Add directed edges
- Detect cycles using DFS
- Perform Topological Sort

---

## 🧠 Concepts Used
- Graph Representation (Adjacency List)
- Depth First Search (DFS)
- Cycle Detection
- Topological Sorting

---

## 🛠️ How to Run

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/dag-implementation.git
cd dag-implementation